import{_ as a,c as r,a as i,w as c,b as s,d as p,r as t,o as d}from"./app.2c70320d.js";const j=JSON.parse('{"title":"","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"elementary/007.md"}'),o={name:"elementary/007.md"},l=s("hr",null,null,-1),v=s("source",{src:"",type:"audio/mpeg"},null,-1),h=s("source",{src:"",type:"audio/mpeg"},null,-1),u=p('<p>The first pairs of jeans were designed for durability.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 牛仔裤最初是为耐用性而被设计出来的。 </div><p>Named for the French city of Nîmes,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 它以法国城市尼姆命名， </div><p>denim was constructed as a sturdy cotton weave worn by sailors.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 牛仔布是水手服装采用的一种结实的棉织品。 </div><p>This rugged material got even stronger in the 19th century,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 在19世纪，这种材料的耐用性变得更佳， </div><p>when Levi Strauss and Jacob Davis added</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 列维·斯特劳斯和雅各布·戴维斯 </div><p>metal rivets to reinforce stress points.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 在服装的应力点添加了金属铆钉用以加固。 </div><p>Their design introduced a new brand of durable trousers</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 他们为加州矿工设计出了一种新的耐用长裤 </div><p>for California miners that could withstand years of wear and tear.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 这种长裤可以经得起多年的磨损。 </div><p>Over the course of the 20th century,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 在20世纪， </div><p>these working-class pants have transformed into fashion icons.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 这种本为工人设计的裤子成为了一种时尚的标志。 </div><p>But as the demand for jeans has gone up,their durability has gone down.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 但随着人们需求的增加，牛仔裤的耐用性也下降了。 </div><p>Today, most pairs last no longer than a year.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 现在的大多数牛仔裤穿不过一年。 </div><p>And each new pair you buy has a much higher cost than you might think.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 并且每一条牛仔裤的代价都出乎意料的高。 </div><p>Every pair of jeans begins its life in a cotton field.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 牛仔裤初始于棉田。 </div><p>It takes about 0.7 kilograms of cotton to produce a single pair of pants.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 生产一条牛仔裤大概需要0.7公斤的棉花。 </div><p>Growing this much cotton requires roughly 10,000 liters of water,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 棉花的种植需要大约 10,000 升水， </div><p>not to mention various herbicides and pesticides,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 更不用说各种除草剂和杀虫剂 </div><p>which can contaminate groundwater.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 对地下水的污染。 </div><p>The cotton is harvested by hand or industrial machines</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 棉花通常通过机器或手工收割， </div><p>and transported to textile factories where it’s spun into yarn.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 然后运到纺织厂织成纱线。 </div><p>At this point, it’s typically combined with plastic fibers like spandex</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 它通常会与氨纶等塑料纤维结合 </div><p>to increase the yarn’s elasticity.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 来增加纱线的弹性。 </div><p>These plastic threads make modern jeans more comfortable and flexible,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 虽然这让牛仔裤变得更加舒适、有弹性， </div><p>but also much less durable.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 但也降低了布料的耐用性。 </div><p>Next, the yarn is dyed jeans’ trademark blue.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 接着，纱线会被染成牛仔裤标志性的蓝色。 </div><p>Historically, this color came from natural plant-derived indigo.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 历史上，这种靛蓝会从天然植物中提取。 </div><p>But most modern manufacturers use a synthetic dye</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 但现在大多数制造商会使用合成染料， </div><p>made from petroleum byproducts and toxic chemicals.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 成分包括各种石油副产品和有毒的化学品。 </div><p>Once dyed, the cotton-plastic blend is woven into denim sheets,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 染色后，布料会被编织成牛仔布， </div><p>which are then cut and sewn into jeans.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 裁剪、缝制后变成牛仔裤。 </div><p>After assembly, some jeans undergo additional procedures</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 组装后，一些牛仔裤 </div><p>to get a distressed look.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 会被做旧、磨损。 </div><p>This often includes chemical sprays and multiple cycles of acid-washing,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 通常化学喷雾和酸洗等过程的堆积物极其有害， </div><p>the toxic runoff can turn rivers indigo-blue.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 连河流都能染成靛蓝色。 </div><p>Finally, there are the zippers, buttons, and rivets</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 最后，拉链、纽扣和铆钉 </div><p>made of copper and other metals,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 由铜和其他金属制成。 </div><p>whose mining is yet another source of environmental degradation.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 它们的开采是环境退化的另一个来源。 </div><p>All in all, the manufacturing process for a single pair of jeans</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 一条牛仔裤的制造过程 </div><p>emits over 33 kilograms of carbon—</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 能排放 33 公斤的碳—— </div><p>the equivalent of drivingover 110 kilometers.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 相当于开车开了110 多公里。 </div><p>But this process doesn&#39;t just damage the environment.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 这过程不仅仅会破坏环境。 </div><p>Much of the world’s cotton is grown in developing countries,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 大部分棉花种植在 </div><p>with poor labor practices and few protections for workers.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 缺乏正当劳动法规的发展中国家。 </div><p>Cotton here is often picked by children or forced labor,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 这里的棉花通常由童工或强制性劳役采摘， </div><p>and most jean manufacturing plants frequently expose workers</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 并且，工人们在生产过程中 </div><p>to toxic chemicals throughout production.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 经常接触有毒的化学品。 </div><p>One particularly dangerous technique called sandblasting</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 其中包括喷砂， </div><p>involves spraying jeans with fine sand at high pressures</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 需要工人们在高压下用细砂喷涂牛仔裤， </div><p>and has been linked with numerous cases of incurable and often fatal lung disease.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 能导致许多无法治愈，通常致命的肺部疾病。 </div><p>Like many globally produced products,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 像许多全球化的产品一样， </div><p>jeans are made in poor countries and bought in rich ones.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 牛仔裤由穷国生产，被富国购买。 </div><p>All these pants will likely be washed dozens or even hundreds of times per year.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 这些裤子每年要洗几十次到几百次。 </div><p>This energy intensive process breaks down the plastics woven into each pair,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 洗衣的过程会分解编制进牛仔裤的塑料， </div><p>releasing microplastics into the water</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 将其释放到水中， </div><p>and, perhaps most ironic of all, shortening the jean’s lifespan.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 最讽刺的可能是缩短了牛仔裤的使用寿命。 </div><p>Like most waste, discarded jeans end up in landfills,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 废弃的牛仔裤会被丢到垃圾填埋场， </div><p>where their decomposition releases methane gas,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 分解的过程中会释放甲烷气体， </div><p>while their dyes and plastics leach into the soil and groundwater.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 染料和塑料则渗入土壤，污染地下水。 </div><p>Some companies are working on solutions here,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 一些公司已经在寻找解决方案了， </div><p>from using organic cotton to recycling and reusing denim.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 其中包括使用有机棉或回收再利用牛仔布。 </div><p>You can also help reduce the environmental impact of your favorite pants</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 你也可以来帮助保护环境， </div><p>by buying used jeans and buying fewer pairs altogether.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 少买几条牛仔裤，或买二手的。 </div><p>Denim manufacturers also recommend only washing your jeans once every 10 wears.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 牛仔布制造商也建议穿满10次再洗。 </div><p>And, when possible, air dry your pants to reduce energy consumption.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 并且晾晒裤子来减少能源消耗。 </div><p>Life cycle and labor problems like these extend far beyond just jeans.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 诸如此类的生命周期和劳动力问题不仅仅是牛仔裤而已。 </div><p>Some governments are pursuing policies to make companies more responsible</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 一些政府正在推行政策， </div><p>for worker pay and welfare,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 让企业对工人的工资和福利负责， </div><p>but unsustainable practices still run rampant throughout the fashion industry.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 但这种做法仍然在时尚界泛滥。 </div><p>So when the price tags on your clothes seem like a steal,</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 所以当你觉得一件衣服的价格太便宜时， </div><p>it’s important to consider who’s actually being robbed.</p><div class="cn-transcript"> 应该思考它真正代价是什么。 </div>',140);function m(f,y,g,w,b,_){const n=t("note-title"),e=t("note-media");return d(),r("div",null,[i(n,{title:"Why do your jeans wear out so quickly?  ",author:"Madhavi Venkatesan",time:"2022-10-22 Wed"}),l,i(e,null,{default:c(()=>[v,h]),_:1}),u])}const T=a(o,[["render",m]]);export{j as __pageData,T as default};
